A four-year-old boy has been hailed a lifesaver after using an iPhone to save his grandfather who collapsed while walking in woods.

Kanden Jones was spending the day with diabetic grandfather Carl in Houston, Texas, when his elderly relative's blood sugar became low and he passed out.

With the pair alone on a walk together and Kanden's parents Christmas shopping, the youngster was the only one able to find help for his grandfather.

