'And at that moment, with my dad being diabetic, I knew something was wrong.'

After the call Kanden's parents rushed to the deer lease where Mr Jones had collapsed, where it took two hours for them to locate the pair.

The family then called an ambulance and managed to get Mr Jones emergency treatment at a nearby hospital before he was sent home.

Carl Jones said: 'I just really think it wasn’t my time to go. I think the good Lord was telling me, ‘Carl, you need wake up".'

